[According to the GIDEON database, the Republic of Korea reported 1964
cases during 1950 to 1969; 475 in 1970; 145 in 1980; 0 during 1984 to 1988.
There were 6 imported cases reported in 1992; 5 (imported, 0 fatal) in
1993; 34 (imported, 0 fatal) in 1994; 74 (6 imported, 0 fatal) in 1995; 7
(5 imported, 0 fatal) in 1996; 10 (0 fatal) in 1997. The 1991 data
referenced in this article are not noted in the database, but the 1970 data
may further support the 10-year cyclical nature of the disease in Korea.
The data for 1950-1969 data are not presented by year, so they cannot be
analyzed for cyclical trends. - Mod.ES
